The paper proposes a distributed multi-object tracking algorithm, which involves sensor networks and fusion of posterior distributions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of multi-Bernoulli filter and covariance intersection techniques indicate that the paper may also be relevant to Computer Vision (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
